cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

The paper deals with online action detection using features extracted from RGBD images and skeletal joints. This suggests that the paper could belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and random forests (RFs) also suggests that the paper could belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also deals with real-time processing, which suggests that it could belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) or robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories.
